scent cover which is the best scent eleminator product line specificly for hunting elk in colorado i've used scent killer and dead downwind brand sprays in the past hunting elk in colorado i have to be straight with you it's hard to know if it worked or not because elk have such incredible hearing along with a good sense of smell i wash my camo's in scent free laundry detergent and hang them out on a line to dry outside then seal them in a zip lock bag i don't put them on until i get close to where i'm going to hunt that works for me when elk hunting and it also seems to work for my hunting buddies i look at it this way hunters didn't have scent killers of any kind years back they were successful anyway hope this helps if just a little btw stay away from powdered carbon that sprinkles on your clothes thats a gimmick and makes a heck of a mess on your clothes and boots Laundry detergent Comanche Soap Laundry Hunting Shotgun Plastic Washing machine Knife Poker jargon Red Deer American Black Bear Elk Grove, California Trapping Genericized trademark Procter & Gamble Sin City Bedbug Dishwasher Olfaction Tobacco Dry cleaning Fox hunting Skunk Professional wrestling match types Internal ballistics Time Out of Mind Textile manufacturing Scent hound Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Kakapo Queen (band) Looney Tunes and Merrie Melodies filmography Phosphorus Fecal incontinence Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Hemp Animal Liberation Front Japanese tea ceremony Illegal drug trade Obedience training Tofu Bread Mushroom hunting Gray Wolf World War Three (Doctor Who) Odor Professional wrestling holds Cat Kayak Camouflage Clothing Climbing equipment Shoe The Lovely Bones Thermal power station Hunter S. Thompson Sodium carbonate Krag-J__rgensen Avalanche Terminal ballistics Foot odor Columbine High School massacre Wildfire Japanese toilet StarCraft Episode VI Orca Perfume Phoebe Halliwell Dog Pittsburgh Steelers Coffee Sulfur Henkel Christmas tree Shoe polish Hannibal Lecter Napoleon Dynamit